correct, people think this network provides anonymity. but even with tor, almost all of your posts are tied to a single identity that you publish content with.
as far as getting started in i2p:

if you are able to reach certain sites, but not others, one possibility is that either a. yourself or b. the site you are trying to reach is experience connectivity issues. this is kind of normal unless it constantly persists. keep retrying.
if it persists, one other possibility is that you are not well integrated into the i2p network. check if you are firewalled, or if your bandwith sharing settings are set a tad low.
one last possibility i can think of is that the hidden service you are trying to reach is experiencing downtime, either temporary or permanent

most of i2p's activity can be found on irc and through p2p filesharing (ie bittorrent). i highly recommend getting an irc client and connecting to irc2p. this will tell you how to do that: http://i2pwiki.i2p/index.php?title=IRC2P
